Pixie-Dust patch for hostapd 2.11.

Forces the WPS enrollee/registrar secret nonces (E-S1/E-S2) to zero instead of
drawing them from the RNG. With predictable nonces, pixiewps recovers the WPS
PIN offline from a single M1-M3 exchange. Stock hostapd uses a strong RNG here
and is not Pixie-vulnerable; this build is used only for WPS lab networks that
opt into the "Pixie-Dust Downgrade".

--- a/src/wps/wps_enrollee.c
+++ b/src/wps/wps_enrollee.c
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@
 	const u8 *addr[4];
 	size_t len[4];

-	if (random_get_bytes(wps->snonce, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN) < 0)
+	if ((os_memset(wps->snonce, 0, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN), 0) < 0)
 		return -1;
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: E-S1", wps->snonce, WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN);
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: E-S2",
